@wilcoln Is there some other way to change the code to make more sense and not work with an invalid AST?
These 2 if conditions are very similar except for these lines from each:

final DetailAST startingDot = ast.getFirstChild();
final DetailAST startingDot = ast.getFirstChild().getNextSibling();

My current idea is the first if statement to change it to:
if (ast.getType() == TokenTypes.IMPORT) {
  if (!allowClassImports) {
    ...
  }
} else if (!allowStaticMemberImports) {
...
}

You agree that there is no reason for non-static imports to go to the else if as it will never be a valid reason?
My second idea was merging the if and else if conditions somehow and only have getNextSibling apply to static imports.

